oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Baptism on Clinch River
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a baptism on the bank of the Clinch River. A preacher and a man are standing in the water in the center. The steamboat "T. L. Brown" is on the left and people are watching the baptism from the decks. A sign on the boat reads, "T.L. Brown of Chattanooga".
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Baptisms; Rivers; Steamboats
